	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-07-17T04:00:29">British Smaller Companies VCT plc is a United Kingdom-based venture capital trust. The principal activity of the Company is making long term equity and loan investments, mainly in unquoted businesses. The Company's objective is to provide investors with an attractive long-term tax free dividend yield while seeking to maintain the capital value of their investment. The investment strategy of the Company is to create a portfolio that blends a mix of companies operating in traditional industries with those that offer opportunities in the application and development of innovation. The Company invests in the United Kingdom businesses across a range of sectors, including software, information technology, telecommunications, business services, manufacturing and industrial services, retail and brands, and healthcare. The Company may also invest in preference shares and loan stock. YFM Private Equity Limited is the Company's investment adviser.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2015-12-14T20:41:28">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 September 2015, British Smaller Companies VCT plc revenues increased from L1.4M to L7.2M. Net income increased from L577K to L6.1M. Revenues reflect Gain on Realisation of Investments increase from L26K to L3M, Gains on investments held at fair value increase from L443K to L2.5M, Interest on Loans to Unquoted Companies increase of 49% to L1M.</Text>
